=begin
  Treasure Window - Real-Time Treasure & Loot Display

  Creates a dedicated window to display treasure objects in the room in
  real time. Automatically updates as treasures appear or disappear, with
  clickable links to interact with loot. Incorporates killtracker output
  (courtesy of Alastir and Nisugi) and provides quick-action commands for
  looting the room or running eloot. Supports both Wrayth FE panel and
  GTK window for Avalon and Wizard FEs.

  References:
    Wrayth FE Window: https://discordapp.com/channels/226045346399256576/1339018254517145681
    GTK Window:       https://discordapp.com/channels/226045346399256576/1386507836191670342

  Usage:
    ;treasurewindow              - Start treasure window

  In-game Commands (while running):
    *click                       - Toggle LOOT ROOM and ELOOT clickable links
    *twcol                       - Toggle single/double column layout
    *twgtk                       - Enable GTK window

  Author: Phocosoen, ChatGPT
  Tags: wrayth, frontend, mod, window, treasures, gems, coins, loot, avalon, wizard, gtk3
  Version: 1.4.2

  Changelog:
  1.4.2 (2025-08-21)
    - Bugfix to ensure ASCII safe characters used in code for ASCII loaded Ruby/FEs.
  1.4.1 (2025-06-25)
    - Replaced light/dark mode toggle with GTK palette selector.
  1.4.0 (2025-06-23)
    - Added Wizard and Avalon FE compatibility via implementation of a GTK window.
  1.3.1 (2025-06-07)
    - Column button removed. Command is *twcol to swap between single and double column layouts.
    - Dead creatures output removed.
    - Layout button added to toggle between one or two column format.
    - Will save state between sessions for all commands.
  1.2.2 (2025-05-06)
    - Fix for Moonsedge bounties.
  1.2.1 (2025-05-02)
    - Added upstream hook to toggle clickable LOOT ROOM and ELOOT commands. Off by default.
  1.2.0 (2025-04-30)
    - Added LOOT ROOM command with automatic empty/fill right hand.
    - Added eloot command.
    - Dead creature output added with click-to-loot.
  1.1.0 (2025-04-26)
    - Killtracker output removed from creaturewindow and moved to treasurewindow.
  1.0.0 (2025-02-11)
    - Initial release.
=end

